JCVI::Range defines an object which converts 5'/3' ends to upper and lower
range, with the strand property. It has evolved to allow several comparison
methods as well.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc JCVI::Range

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/JCVI-Range

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=JCVI-Range

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/JCVI-Range

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/JCVI-Range

